docs.abstract: The contrast of National Day pageantry in Beijing versus anti-government mayhem in Hong Kong was almost certainly infuriating to President Xi Jinping.
docs.snippet: The contrast of National Day pageantry in Beijing versus anti-government mayhem in Hong Kong was almost certainly infuriating to President Xi Jinping.
docs.lead_paragraph: BEIJING — China’s authoritarian president used the 70th anniversary of Communist Party rule on Tuesday to pledge that nothing would stop his nation’s ascent. But the message was marred by some of the worst anti-government violence to convulse Hong Kong, including the first police shooting of a protester.

headline.main: Protests Erupt in Hong Kong, Overshadowing China’s National Day Parade
headline.print_headline: On Chinese Holiday, Violence Offsets Pageantry
